\begin{frame}[fragile]
  \frametitle{Descriptive statistics}
Calculate the mean of \texttt{Age}:
\begin{verbatim}
> mean(Age)
Error in mean(Age) : object 'Age' not
found
\end{verbatim}
You must tell \texttt{R} that \texttt{Age} is a variable (column) 
\emph{within} \texttt{issp.df}, i.e.
\begin{Schunk}
\begin{Sinput}
> mean(issp.df$Age)
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
[1] NA
\end{Soutput}
\end{Schunk}
You must also tell \texttt{R} how to deal with missing values, i.e.
\begin{Schunk}
\begin{Sinput}
> mean(issp.df$Age, na.rm = TRUE)
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
[1] 45.77179
\end{Soutput}
\end{Schunk}
\end{frame}
\begin{frame}[fragile]
  \frametitle{Frequency Table}
\begin{Schunk}
\begin{Sinput}
> table(issp.df$Gender)
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
     Female        Male NA, refused 
        607         418          22 
\end{Soutput}
\begin{Sinput}
> sum(table(issp.df$Gender))
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
[1] 1047
\end{Soutput}
\begin{Sinput}
> table(issp.df$Gender)/sum(table(issp.df$Gender))
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
     Female        Male NA, refused 
 0.57975167  0.39923591  0.02101242 
\end{Soutput}
\end{Schunk}
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}[fragile]
  \frametitle{Frequency Table}
Tired of typing \texttt{issp.df\$} over and over again? Use the \texttt{with} function.
\begin{Schunk}
\begin{Sinput}
> with(issp.df, table(Gender)/sum(table(Gender)))
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
Gender
     Female        Male NA, refused 
 0.57975167  0.39923591  0.02101242 
\end{Soutput}
\end{Schunk}
Turn it into percentages, keep only 1 decimal place.
\begin{Schunk}
\begin{Sinput}
> gender.pct <- with(issp.df, 
                    table(Gender)/sum(table(Gender)))
> round(gender.pct*100, 1)
\end{Sinput}
\begin{Soutput}
Gender
     Female        Male NA, refused 
       58.0        39.9         2.1 
\end{Soutput}
\end{Schunk}
\end{frame}

